						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the Mahāliṅgēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record mentions about the construction of a tank and prohibition of fishing therein. It refers to the temple of Huttūru and to <hi rend="bold">Pāṇḍyarasa.</hi> The extant portion of the date mentions the cyclic year Sādhāraṇa.</p>						

						</summary>
